cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper focuses on visual localization, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method also involves learning techniques and optimization, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system is designed to be adaptable to available computational resources, which suggests a potential application in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the evaluation involves large benchmarking datasets, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
